<p>Capgemini said it will sell its US subsidiary Capgemini Government Solutions, which has worked for the US Immigration and Customs Enforcement agency, and that the divestment process will begin immediately. The decision follows public and political pressure in France for the company to clarify the subsidiary’s ICE-related work amid broader scrutiny of ICE enforcement methods. Several outlets linked the intensified attention to fatalities connected to ICE operations, which helped fuel calls for transparency and accountability around such contracts.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/bA39lVLMrqRnxA7usk19YecSwNfv1CZnGDiaeQDa7k2GI071qB-nXjcRNJbXtqx5alQaT8VvE1-PDXl2Shy-J5bH60CY9GAGLyzu_fMvuAbOODAcb95v5YnyUTNftKIX4D_TQJZD0DvT9lDClu9y5pIFXpsXOus0hboniivsN_NpltHBspFPqaMFVISrnV3yZeUtXFxprpxwAbC1ciPhO04FZ-tJGugnOR2i2-cuhXulkqNYDjunTTTb3Ehh5E77tPUdGKaz-QMR4N2yhg' alt='A photo used to illustrate reporting on Capgemini’s planned divestment of its US government-services unit.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>French political scrutiny: French lawmakers, including Finance Minister Roland Lescure, publicly asked Capgemini to shed light on the ICE contract signed by its US government-services arm.</li><li>Company messaging: Capgemini said it was initiating the divestment immediately, while reporting did not definitively attribute the sale to the ICE contract itself.</li><li>Triggering incidents: Reporting connected the spike in concern to a Minnesota incident in which two US citizens were fatally shot last month, after which ICE tactics drew renewed attention.</li><li>Human rights spotlight: The company’s move comes as international debate continues over the methods used by the US immigration enforcement agency ICE, placing additional reputational focus on vendors that support it.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Capgemini: The company says it will sell Capgemini Government Solutions and start the divestment process immediately, without publicly pinning the decision to the ICE contract in the reporting. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/capgemini-to-sell-us-unit-linked-to-ice/article70577903.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>French lawmakers and government figures: French politicians pressed the firm to explain the ICE-linked contract, reflecting concern about enforcement tactics and the public-interest stakes of corporate involvement. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3342006/frances-capgemini-sell-us-subsidiary-under-pressure-ice-contract'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Media and public scrutiny around ICE: Coverage frames the sale as part of a wider wave of scrutiny of ICE operations and their consequences, including deaths reported in connection with ICE actions. (<a href='https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260201-french-company-capgemini-to-sell-us-subsidiary-amid-controversy-over-ice-links'>RFI</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cd9e4xw8vqqo'>French tech giant Capgemini to sell US subsidiary working for ICE</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3342006/frances-capgemini-sell-us-subsidiary-under-pressure-ice-contract'>France’s Capgemini to sell US subsidiary under pressure for ICE contract</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260201-french-company-capgemini-to-sell-us-subsidiary-amid-controversy-over-ice-links'>French company Capgemini to sell US subsidiary amid controversy over ICE links</a> - rfi.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/capgemini-to-sell-us-unit-linked-to-ice/article70577903.ece'>Capgemini to sell U.S. unit linked to ICE</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1qsuyiw/french_it_giant_capgemini_to_sell_us_subsidiary/'>French IT giant Capgemini to sell US subsidiary after row over ICE links</a> - reddit.com</li></ul>